<h2><span style="font-size:16pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif"><span style="color:#000000">Decentralisation-PRI and ULB</span></span></span></h2>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<h4><span style="font-size:12pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif"><span style="color:#666666">Intro</span></span></span></h4>
<p><span style="font-size:13pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif"><span style="color:#000000">It's been more than 25 years since grassroot democracy in the form of ULB and PRI became a Constitutional imperative (73rd and 74th C.A)</span></span></span></p>
<h3><span style="font-size:13.999999999999998pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif"><span style="color:#6d9eeb">Decentralisation at three levels- Functions, Finances and Functionaries</span></span></span></h3>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<h4><span style="font-size:12pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif"><span style="color:#666666">Benefits:</span></span></span></h4>
<ul>
<li style="list-style-type:disc"><span style="font-size:13pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif"><span style="color:#000000">taps into biggest strength of India-Diversity</span></span></span></li>
<li style="list-style-type:disc"><span style="font-size:13pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif"><span style="color:#000000">participative democracy leading to better resource utilisation</span></span></span></li>
<li style="list-style-type:disc"><span style="font-size:13pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif"><span style="color:#000000">safeguard traditions and cultural heritage.e.g: tribal practices</span></span></span></li>
<li style="list-style-type:disc"><span style="font-size:13pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif"><span style="color:#000000">Political empowerment of Women and SC/ST</span></span></span></li>
<li style="list-style-type:disc"><span style="font-size:13pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif"><span style="color:#000000">Greater accountability and sense of belonging</span></span></span></li>
<li style="list-style-type:disc"><span style="font-size:13pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif"><span style="color:#000000">allows innovation in governance rather than one size fits all. (</span></span></span><a href="https://www.thehindu.com/news/national/other-states/amla-candy-rescues-assam-nutrition-drive/article29426876.ece" style="text-decoration:none"><span style="font-size:13pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif"><span style="color:#1155cc"><u>Amla + Gur</u></span></span></span></a><span style="font-size:13pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif"><span style="color:#000000"> as alternative to folic acid supplements for anaemia at District level)</span></span></span></li>
<li style="list-style-type:disc"><span style="font-size:13pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif"><span style="color:#000000">Best performing districts give models for others</span></span></span><a href="https://darpg.gov.in/sites/default/files/Book-on-Innovations-released-by-Hon'ble-PM-on-CSD,2017.pdf" style="text-decoration:none"><span style="font-size:13pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif"><span style="color:#1155cc"><u>. (Ratna Dantia Abhiyan in Datia. Social justice at doorsteps</u></span></span></span></a><span style="font-size:13pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif"><span style="color:#000000">)&nbsp;</span></span></span></li>
<li style="list-style-type:disc"><span style="font-size:13pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif"><span style="color:#000000">Cooperative federalism at state level + competitive federalism at district level</span></span></span></li>
<li style="list-style-type:disc"><span style="font-size:13pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif"><span style="color:#000000">PESA allows political justice by giving rights to tribals over their resources</span></span></span></li>
<li style="list-style-type:disc"><span style="font-size:13pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif"><span style="color:#000000">bottom up planning instead of top down approach</span></span></span></li></ul>
<h4><span style="font-size:12pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif"><span style="color:#666666">Issues:</span></span></span></h4>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<ol>
<li style="list-style-type:decimal"><span style="font-size:13pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif"><span style="color:#000000">Administrative&nbsp;</span></span></span>
<ol>
<li style="list-style-type:lower-alpha"><span style="font-size:13pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif"><span style="color:#000000">Answerability : to public! But as of now, only answerable to State Government. State government lack of initiative- calling ward meeting, financial devolution or elections</span></span></span></li>
<li style="list-style-type:lower-alpha"><span style="font-size:13pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif"><span style="color:#000000">SPVs for central schemes overshadow their roles&nbsp;</span></span></span></li>
<li style="list-style-type:lower-alpha"><span style="font-size:13pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif"><span style="color:#000000">Decentralised corruption</span></span></span></li></ol></li>
<li style="list-style-type:decimal"><span style="font-size:13pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif"><span style="color:#000000">Financing: amount inadequate + inflexible + capacity building fund? + empowerment for local tax?&nbsp;</span></span></span></li></ol>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<ol start="3">
<li style="list-style-type:decimal"><span style="font-size:13pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif"><span style="color:#000000">Design weakness: Constitution powers the States to devolve functions and responsibilities to them through law. (counter: Given diverse habitation patterns, political and social history, it makes sense to mandate States to assign functions to local governments)</span></span></span></li>
<li style="list-style-type:decimal"><span style="font-size:13pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif"><span style="color:#000000">Political&nbsp;</span></span></span>
<ol>
<li style="list-style-type:lower-alpha"><span style="font-size:13pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif"><span style="color:#000000">Delay in elections: States postponing elections. Violation of the constitutional mandate of five yearly elections and SC judgements. In 2005, when the Gujarat government postponed the Ahmedabad corporation elections, a Supreme Court constitutional bench held that under no circumstances can such postponements be allowed. Similarly Tamil Nadu were not held for 2 years. This further reduces grants of Finance commission.</span></span></span></li>
<li style="list-style-type:lower-alpha"><span style="font-size:13pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif"><span style="color:#000000">Panchayat Patis: proxy candidates in places of mandatory seats for women.&nbsp;</span></span></span></li>
<li style="list-style-type:lower-alpha"><span style="font-size:13pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif"><span style="color:#000000">has provided a conduit for criminals to enter politics&nbsp;</span></span></span></li>
<li style="list-style-type:lower-alpha"><span style="font-size:13pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif"><span style="color:#000000">gram sabha meetings not held periodically or composite sabhas covering multiple villages cause dip in participants</span></span></span></li></ol></li></ol>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<ol start="5">
<li style="list-style-type:decimal"><span style="font-size:13pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif"><span style="color:#000000">Capacity building related&nbsp;</span></span></span>
<ol>
<li style="list-style-type:lower-alpha"><span style="font-size:13pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif"><span style="color:#000000">Gram Sabha members are not educated enough to discuss developmental processes in sabha meetings</span></span></span></li></ol></li></ol>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><span style="font-size:13pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif"><span style="color:#000000">Solutions:</span></span></span></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<ol>
<li style="list-style-type:decimal"><span style="font-size:13pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif"><span style="color:#000000">Technology: new systems of SMS, or social media groups, Video recording could be used for facilitating discussions between members of a grama sabha, app to give details like minutes of meeting of Gram Sabha to every elector in the Gram unit.&nbsp;</span></span></span>
<ol>
<li style="list-style-type:lower-alpha"><span style="font-size:13pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif"><span style="color:#000000">#eg : Spatial Planning Application called ‘Gram Manchitra’ which is a Geo Spatial based decision support system for panchayats.</span></span></span></li></ol></li>
<li style="list-style-type:decimal"><span style="font-size:13pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif"><span style="color:#000000">Panchayats are burdened with a huge amount of work that other departments thrust on them, without being compensated for the extra administrative costs.</span></span></span></li>
<li style="list-style-type:decimal"><span style="font-size:13pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif"><span style="color:#000000">we cannot have accountable GPs, without local taxation. Local governments are reluctant to collect property taxes and user charges fully.</span></span></span></li>
<li style="list-style-type:decimal"><span style="font-size:13pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif"><span style="color:#000000">bottomup planning</span></span></span></li>
<li style="list-style-type:decimal"><span style="font-size:13pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif"><span style="color:#000000">quorum in Gram Sabha meeting</span></span></span></li>
<li style="list-style-type:decimal"><span style="font-size:13pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif"><span style="color:#000000">make centers contribution through Finance Commission dependent on State progress on local governance</span></span></span></li>
<li style="list-style-type:decimal"><span style="font-size:13pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif"><span style="color:#000000">addition to Central list on sources of revenue for all Local bodies.</span></span></span></li>
<li style="list-style-type:decimal"><span style="font-size:13pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif"><span style="color:#000000">#eg : Village Secretariat system by Andhra</span></span></span></li></ol>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<h4><span style="font-size:12pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif"><span style="color:#666666">Conclusion:</span></span></span></h4>
<p><span style="font-size:13pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif"><span style="color:#000000">The highest ideal as Mahatma Gandhi envisaged is to transform each village into a self sufficient republic- a Gram Swaraj.</span></span></span></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>